---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="MIAR Legal, Privacy, and Access Notice"
  description="MIAR privacy, access, and jurisdiction notice for the public website and waitlist."
  current="legal"
>
  <main class="subpage-shell legal-shell">
    <section class="subpage-hero legal-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal Notice</p>
      <h1>Privacy, access, and jurisdiction for the public MIAR site.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        This notice covers the public MIAR website and the request-access form. It is meant to
        be practical and narrow: it explains what information is collected here, who can review
        it, who cannot, and when access may be refused or withdrawn.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-grid" aria-label="Legal notice sections">
      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">What This Site Is</p>
        <h2>Public landing page, not open self-service access</h2>
        <p>
          MIAR is presented here as a public information and access-request site. Submitting the
          form does not create an account, contract, evaluation right, or guaranteed follow-up.
          Access requests are reviewed case by case.
        </p>
        <p>
          Separate written terms may apply to any pilot, demonstration, data-sharing arrangement,
          or production use of the platform.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Information Collected</p>
        <h2>Only the information needed to review a request and secure the site</h2>
        <p>The current request-access form collects the details you choose to submit, including:</p>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>Name, work email, organization, and role.</li>
          <li>Operational interest, monitoring focus, timing, and free-text use case notes.</li>
          <li>Technical request metadata such as referrer, user agent, and approximate country, region, and city derived from the request.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Do not submit classified, export-controlled, or other sensitive information through this
          public form.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">How It Is Used</p>
        <h2>Access review, contact, operations, and security</h2>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>To review whether there is a credible organizational or mission fit.</li>
          <li>To contact you about your request where follow-up is warranted.</li>
          <li>To maintain basic records of inbound requests and reduce abuse or spam.</li>
          <li>To protect the site, investigate misuse, and enforce access restrictions.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Who Gets Access</p>
        <h2>Need-to-know internal review only</h2>
        <p>Your submission may be accessed by:</p>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>ReachDefence personnel involved in site administration, access review, or business follow-up.</li>
          <li>Service providers or contractors helping host, secure, or maintain the site, where access is necessary for that work and subject to confidentiality controls.</li>
          <li>Advisers or authorities where disclosure is required to comply with law, protect rights, or respond to abuse or security issues.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Who Does Not</p>
        <h2>No public publication or unrelated third-party sharing</h2>
        <ul class="legal-list">
          <li>Submissions are not intended for public display.</li>
          <li>Submission data is not sold.</li>
          <li>Submission data is not shared with unrelated third parties for advertising or general marketing distribution.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Eligibility</p>
        <h2>Who may request access, and who may be refused</h2>
        <p>
          This site is intended for lawful organizational use, including government, defence,
          research, industrial, and approved partner evaluation workflows. ReachDefence may deny,
          defer, or revoke access where identity, organization, intended use, or jurisdiction
          cannot be validated or appears inconsistent with platform risk controls.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Jurisdictions</p>
        <h2>Access may be restricted by country or legal risk</h2>
        <p>
          MIAR is not offered in every jurisdiction. ReachDefence may block or refuse requests
          based on geography, sanctions, export-control concerns, compliance requirements, or
          security risk.
        </p>
        <p>
          As currently configured for this site, access requests from restricted jurisdictions,
          including China and Pakistan, are not accepted.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="article-body legal-card">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Retention And External Services</p>
        <h2>Kept as needed for review and operations</h2>
        <p>
          Request data may be retained for as long as reasonably needed to review requests,
          maintain operational records, and protect the site. The site may also rely on hosting,
          delivery, and security providers that process technical request data to serve and protect
          the service.
        </p>
        <p>
          External links and third-party websites have their own terms and privacy practices.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-cta">
      <div class="article-body legal-callout">
        <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-compact">Form Notice</p>
        <p>
          By using the request-access form, you confirm that the information you submit is yours
          to share for contact and access-review purposes and that you are not sending sensitive
          material through a public intake channel.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a class="button button-primary" href="/#waitlist">Return to request access</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
